<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1087,1545]" box="[151,577,1087,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName authority="Guerin-Meneville, 1843" authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,577,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[151,299,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">Perla pallida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[307,577,1087,1113]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="393 - 395" refId="ref13241" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1843) Genre Perle. In: Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (Ed.), Iconographie du Regne Animal de G. Cuvier. Insectes, 1843, pp. 393 - 395." type="journal article" year="1843">Guérin-Méneville, 1843</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1087,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">
The species was described without exact locality, mentioned only as ’Caucasus’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[1150,1424,1123,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="393 - 395" refId="ref13241" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1843) Genre Perle. In: Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (Ed.), Iconographie du Regne Animal de G. Cuvier. Insectes, 1843, pp. 393 - 395." type="journal article" year="1843">Guérin-Méneville 1843</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, T." box="[151,313,1158,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="136 - 192" refId="ref15025" refString="Walker, T. (1851) Sub-order 2. Perlides. In: Gray, J. E. (Ed.), Catalogue of the specimens of Neuropterous Insects in the Collection of the British Museum. Part I. Phryganides-Perlides. Trustees, London, pp. 136 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1851">Walker (1851)</bibRefCitation>
found its types in the Natural History Museum, London (NHM), though they were lacking from the latest catalog (
<bibRefCitation author="Kimmins, D. E." box="[310,478,1195,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="337 - 361" refId="ref13843" refString="Kimmins, D. E. (1970) A list of type specimens of Plecoptera and Megaloptera in the British Museum (Natural History). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), 24 (8), 337 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 1524" type="journal article" year="1970">Kimmins 1970</bibRefCitation>
) and, presumably lost during the 19th century. 
<bibRefCitation author="Klapalek, F." box="[995,1176,1195,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref13935" refString="Klapalek, F. (1923) Plecopteres II. Fam. Perlidae. Subfam. Perlinae, Subfam. Neoperlinae. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, 4 (2), 1 - 193." type="journal article" year="1923">Klapálek (1923)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species on the basis of specimens from Azerbaijan, 
<collectingCountry box="[643,733,1231,1257]" name="Georgia" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">Georgia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[787,869,1231,1257]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. Though some question the conspecificity of these specimens, they have become de facto 
<typeStatus box="[587,687,1267,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">neotypes</typeStatus>
on which the present concept of the species is based (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref14690" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2002) The species of Perla (Plecoptera: Perlidae): evidence from egg morphology. Scopolia, 49, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2002">Sivec &amp; Stark 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Klapálek’s Azerbaijan specimen was a male collected in Gəncə (Gəncə-Qazax region, original labels: Elisabethop; Kolenati; caucasica / det. Kempny; pallida / Klapálek) and still exists in the Natural History Museum of Wien (NHMW). One of us (DM) studied and compared Klapálek’s specimens with our recent specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,244,1411,1437]" name="Georgia" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">Georgia</collectingCountry>
. Besides the NHMW specimen from the 19th century, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kasymov, A. G." box="[865,1055,1411,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" refId="ref13600" refString="Kasymov, A. G. (1972) Presnovadnaya fauna Kavkaza. Elm, Baku, 288 pp." type="book" year="1972">Kasymov (1972)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from several sites in Gəncə-Qazax (Dəstəfur), Kəlbəcər-Laçın (Kəlbəcər, Tərtərçay River), Lənkəran (Sahgadzhi), Şəki-Zaqatala (Katexçay River) and Yuxarı-Qarabağ regions (Şuşa, Xankəndi). 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[878,1116,1483,1509]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref14690" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2002) The species of Perla (Plecoptera: Perlidae): evidence from egg morphology. Scopolia, 49, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="2002">Sivec &amp; Stark (2002)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guerin-Meneville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1250,1356,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Perla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">
<emphasis box="[1250,1356,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">P. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a species complex that is distributed in the Caucasus, 
<collectingCountry box="[732,831,1519,1545]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="62">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
, the Balkans and the Carpathians.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
